sentences: Ralph Moore (born 24 December 1956) is an English jazz saxophonist.
In 1972, he moved to Santa Maria, California, to live with his father.
"Around 1975 he moved to Boston, where he played locally and attended the Berklee College of Music.
Moore began his professional career with a tour of Scandinavia in 1979.
He was part of Horace Silver's band from 1981 to 1985, including for tours of Europe and Japan, and recordings.

He then played with numerous musicians, including Roy Haynes (around 1982–86), Darrell Grant (1986–87), Dizzy Gillespie's reunion band (1987), Freddie Hubbard (around 1987–91), and Gene Harris (1989–90).
